  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Customer Service Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Customer Service Officer</strong></p><p><strong>Job Highlights</strong></p><ul><li>Career development opportunities</li><li>Open, friendly and dynamic work environment</li><li>Attractive salary that commensurate with experience and skills</li></ul><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Handle incoming calls, emails, and walk-in enquiries professionally, serving as the first point of contact for families and guiding enquiries towards confirmed appointments</li><li>Support coordination between clients and funeral directors to ensure smooth communication</li><li>Deliver consistent service standards and support the team in maintaining service excellence across all client touchpoints</li><li>Perform basic administrative duties and other ad-hoc tasks as required</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Is empathetic, calm, and respectful with clients</li><li>Communicates clearly and is comfortable is client-facing roles</li><li>Is organised, reliable, and follows through on tasks</li><li>Has basic proficiency in Word and Excel</li><li>Has customer service or call centre experience (preferred)</li><li>Is eager to learn and grow in a service-oriented role</li><li>Can converse in English, Chinese, and dialects</li></ul><p>Interested applicants are invited to send your resume to our HR department at careers@directfuneral.com.sg to find out more. We regret that only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</p>",
